<span id="freeTextContainer14532548164461609223">The premise of the novel is that waiting is an emotion. By the end of the book, I was ready to concede the point to the author as this was one of the most exasperating stories I&apos;ve ever read. I really wearied of waiting for the culmination of the story. It&apos;s well written, that&apos;s not the issue. The story just drove me insane as we waited and waited and waited for Lin to get a spine and marry the woman he claimed to love. And she just dutifully waited and waited and waited....<br/><br/>In all seriousness, t</span>
  <span id="freeText14532548164461609223" style="display:none">The premise of the novel is that waiting is an emotion. By the end of the book, I was ready to concede the point to the author as this was one of the most exasperating stories I've ever read. I really wearied of waiting for the culmination of the story. It's well written, that's not the issue. The story just drove me insane as we waited and waited and waited for Lin to get a spine and marry the woman he claimed to love. And she just dutifully waited and waited and waited....<br /><br />In all seriousness, the author provided a perfect story to illustrate his point of view. It still drove me crazy. </span>
